Kareemah Yasmina BELL, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. Stacie BELL, Defendant-Appellee. No. 07-1421. United States Court of Appeals, Fourth Circuit. Submitted: Aug. 30, 2007. Decided: Sept. 5, 2007. Kareemah Yasmina Bell, Appellant Pro Se. Before MICHAEL, KING, and SHEDD, Circuit Judges.

Affirmed by unpublished PER CURIAM opinion.

Unpublished opinions are not binding precedent in this circuit.

PER CURIAM:

Kareemah Yasmina Bell appeals the district court’s order dismissing her employment discrimination action for failure to state a claim. We have reviewed the record and find no reversible error. Accordingly, we affirm for the reasons stated by the district court. Bell v. Bell, No. 1:06-cv-01369-CHM (E.D. Va. filed Mar. 30, 2007; entered Apr. 3, 2007). We dispense with oral argument because the facts and legal contentions are adequately presented *994in the materials before the court and argument would not aid the decisional process.

AFFIRMED.
